cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the performance of genetic and evolutionary algorithms on fitness landscapes. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of optimization algorithms to find the global optimum of NK fitness landscapes. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper analyzes the performance of different algorithms on a specific type of problem instance. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of estimation of distribution algorithms, which are a type of machine learning algorithm. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the optimization of fitness landscapes, which can be relevant in game theory.
